
[1]speculate

   SPEC'ULATE, v.i. [L. speculor, to view, to contemplate, from specio, to
   see.]

   1. To meditate; to contemplate; to consider a subject by turning it in
   the mind and viewing it in its different aspects and relations; as, to
   speculate on political events; to speculate on the probable results of
   a discovery.

   2. In commerce, to purchase land, goods, stock or other things, with
   the expectation of an advance in price, and of selling the articles
   with a profit by means of such advance; as, to speculate in coffee, or
   in sugar, or in six percent stock, or in bank stock.
